# Hero image Early Hint removed 2026-04-19: HTTP Link: headers don't support
# `media` queries, so an Early Hint fires on every viewport — mobile would
# download the collage even though the mobile layout is text-only (Scripture
# Alive pattern). Desktop keeps preload via HTML <link media="(min-width:
# 1024px)"> in src/pages/index.astro. Trade: desktop loses the 20-30% Early
# Hint LCP win; mobile gains a guarantee of zero hero bytes. Desktop was
# already scoring 100 — the trade favors mobile.

# ─── Long cache for hashed/immutable assets ────────────────────────────
# CF Pages default is max-age=14400 (4h) which wastes bandwidth re-downloading
# hashed, content-addressed assets on every revisit. PSI flagged 2.3 MB of
# savings from extending these lifetimes.
/_astro/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/favicon-final.svg
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000

/favicon.ico
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000

/og/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000

/images/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000
